Adrian,

Hurrahh, somebody talking some sense. F=MA cannot be violated. If you add
inertia in one portion of the system, you should remove some in another.
Lower mass means more accelleration off the line = higher gas mileage. With
CW crank, motor should idle very smoothly anyway.

Chris
